The paper deals with secret-key capacity in a joint source-channel coding setup, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the wiretap channel model, which is a common model in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of side information and correlated sources is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the sub-category of signal processing and information retrieval (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian codebooks, which is a topic related to multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a separation-based coding scheme, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
